cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on unsupervised learning using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses applications related to computer vision (texture modeling, artistic style transferring, face modeling), which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of discriminative learning, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a synthesis-by-classification algorithm, which is related to graph-based learning, suggesting that cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is a possible sub-category as well.
